general the company was founded in to provide custom programming services and  in  it began to design  develop  market and support automated business management systems for distributors  wholesalers and dealers 
the company s revenue is derived primarily from the sale of prophet systems  maintenance contracts which provide for software support and equipment maintenance  and the sale of optional software products 
each prophet system includes the prophet software  an ibm rs computer  various optional third party software products and hardware components  training  support and installation 
the company s cost of revenue consists principally of the costs of hardware components  customer support  installation and training and  to a lesser extent  third party software 
the company implemented a strategic decision early in to move from its internally developed proprietary hardware system to an open system platform  based on the unix aix operating system running on an ibm rs computer 
the company s adoption of an open system solution broadened the market for the prophet systems  facilitated greater customer acceptance  and allowed successful integration of industry standard third party software and hardware 
in fiscal  the company introduced its next generation product  prophet acclaim  a complete business management system that combines the functionality of the traditional prophet system with the technology of progress software corporation s dbms 
prophet acclaim is targeted for sales to new and current customers 
it has been designed so that current customers can move to this new product while preserving their existing technology infrastructure 
